OpenWRT Install and Maintenance Scripts
=======================================

Why?
----

OpenWRT is well-developed and supported embedded Linux
distribution. However, deployment of it real-world condition faces
some challanges, like ease of initial setup and portability between
different hardware devices. These scripts are intended to simplify
and streamline initial setup and following re-setup of OpenWRT on
various supported devices, reusing and establishing best practices
for deployment and system management. The scripts are intended to
serve as executable documentation - to be human readable and
twekable, and easy to follow step by step in manual mode. At the
same time, once needed configuration is established, the scripts
can provided automated means to install and configure OpenWRT on
any number devices, or recover/resetup and node from scratch.
